    "summary": "Playing games has never been enough for me. \n\nIf I would describe myself in one sentence, I would probably say that I am a curious and adventurous person, yet, I would never happen in a real-life game adventure, as I like to overthink ((pre)calculate) and come up with hundreds of scenarios to modify basically everything in my life. \n\nIn game context, that translates to my favourite RPG role being mage support, who, combining calculations, cunning strategies and strong aid skills, indirectly turns the tide of any battle. \n\nHowever, I have always wanted to influence the experience more than just what is possible. And that is how I met design, specifically game and UX. \n\nIn my opinion, the game and the development role have a lot in common - empowering the user, via different strategies and scenarios, to experience a win (which takes different shape in every situation) in a unique way. \n\nThus, my game and UX design approach is a combination of rational design (calculation and analyses) and situational design (user/player experience and psychology). \n\nI value designs that combine both, as they are both intuitive and innovative, thus excelling above the rest. \n\nIf you spent a few minutes reading this, I would kindly invite you to present me with a few more minutes and check out my work, I am always open to dicussions and new experiences!",
