            "description": "Snuast is a physics-based puzzle game, developed in a team for a week for Saxion UAS. The main game dynamic is utilizing gravity holes to control a character from point A to point B.\nIn this project I entered a premade team, since I wanted to test my adaptability skills, as if I was hired in a new studio. My responsibilities included game systems design, level design, UX/UI and game prototyping. During this project we had a very limited time, so planning was key. We managed to finish almost everything we planned in a good quality. The biggest takeaway from this project is that game and level design are a highly iterative disciplines. Unless you are a magician or industry veteran, you will most probably have a few pitfalls in your design, which you might not be able to see. For this reason, testing and analyzing is crucial. During this project, I did multiple tests on the levels, constantly iterating on these, and even so there were still things that could be done better.",
