            "description": "Gemancer is a solo project, developed for the Game Design course (Saxion UAS) in Flowlab. It is a 2D platformer, in which you have to utilize a special power \u2013 earth wave, at your advantage, to explore the Devil\u2019s Throat cave, collect gems and use them to power the teleporter, to return to the overworld.\nSince it was an individual project, I did visual scripting, game systems design, level design, UI/UX and some asset design. In the process of development, it was my first time planning it all by myself and doing visual scripting. The latter provided an interesting challenge, since my visual scripting skills at that time limited the difficulty mechanics I could implemented. Exactly this made me think outside of the box and think of a simple, yet interesting and rather innovative core game mechanic, like the earth wave. \nA main takeaway from the project is how too much freedom, given to a certain dynamic, makes it harder to understand and use correctly. Feeling of freedom is a powerful aesthetic, which can make an experience enjoyable, however it can also make it confusing, if not dosed properly. In this game, I gave too much freedom to the use of earth waves (every earth chunk that the player can bump into), which made the puzzles a bit intimidating. Still, it was refered as unique and innovative by both my teacher and classmates.",
